1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,331
When an architect gets an idea for a new building, he makes a preliminary drawing.

2
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:10,291
When a creative advertising person gets an idea for a new TV commercial,

3
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:17,891
he puts it into storyboard form, a series of drawings that suggest what the idea will look like in finished form.

4
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,570
Writers with idea prepare a first draft.

5
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:25,251
NOTE Shape up the idea on paper.

6
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:27,971
There are two excellent reasons for this.

7
00:00:28,161 --> 00:00:33,811
When the idea takes tangible form, you can literally look at it, see the loopholes,

8
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:36,371
see what it needs in the way of polish.

9
00:00:36,641 --> 00:00:46,130
Then, too, ideas have to be sold to someone—customers, employees, the boss, friends, fellow club members, investors.

10
00:00:46,480 --> 00:00:50,771
Somebody must buy the idea, else it has no value.

11
00:00:51,201 --> 00:00:55,650
One summer, I was contacted by two life insurance salesmen.

12
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:58,851
Both wanted to work on my insurance program.

13
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:03,171
Both promised to return with a plan for making the needed changes.

14
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:07,010
The first salesman gave me strictly an oral presentation.

15
00:01:07,201 --> 00:01:09,650
He told me in words what I needed.

16
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:11,650
But I soon was confused.

17
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:18,530
He brought in taxes, options, social security, all the technical details of insurance programming.

18
00:01:18,721 --> 00:01:22,130
Frankly, he lost me, and I had to say no.

19
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:25,251
The second salesman used a different approach.

20
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:27,731
He had charted his recommendations.

21
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:31,090
All the details were shown in diagram form.

22
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:36,771
I could grasp his proposal easily and quickly because I could literally see it.

23
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:38,130
He sold me.

24
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:42,050
Resolve to put your ideas in saleable form.

25
00:01:42,161 --> 00:01:52,291
An idea written or in some sort of picture or diagram form has many times more selling power than the idea presented only in oral form.

